        "### Computing $R^2$, Adjusted $R^2$, SSE, MSE, AIC, BIC, $C_p$, and PRESS\n",
        "\n",
        "These quantities can be read from a fitted model, but it is useful to compute them directly from the residuals and leverage values."
      ],
      "id": "d4ff77fa"
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "metadata": {},
      "source": [
        "fit_metrics = fit_categorical\n",
        "y = fit_metrics.model.endog\n",
        "n = fit_metrics.nobs\n",
        "p = fit_metrics.df_model + 1\n",
        "\n",
        "sse = np.sum(fit_metrics.resid ** 2)\n",
        "sst = np.sum((y - y.mean()) ** 2)\n",
        "mse = sse / fit_metrics.df_resid\n",
        "r2 = 1 - sse / sst\n",
        "adj_r2 = 1 - (sse / fit_metrics.df_resid) / (sst / (n - 1))\n",
        "aic = fit_metrics.aic\n",
        "bic = fit_metrics.bic\n",
        "cp = mallows_cp(fit_metrics, sigma2_full)\n",
        "press = np.sum(\n",
        "    (fit_metrics.resid / (1 - fit_metrics.get_influence().hat_matrix_diag)) ** 2\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "pd.Series(\n",
        "    {\n",
        "        \"R^2\": r2,\n",
        "        \"Adjusted R^2\": adj_r2,\n",
        "        \"SSE\": sse,\n",
        "        \"MSE\": mse,\n",
        "        \"AIC\": aic,\n",
        "        \"BIC\": bic,\n",
        "        \"Cp\": cp,\n",
        "        \"PRESS\": press,\n",
        "    }\n",
        ")"
      ],
